modules.description: This module provides a function `f` to create commit info values with a specified author, formatted message, and automatically generated timestamp. It operates on commit info structures using a context module `C` that supplies the current time. Useful for generating detailed commit metadata in MirageOS-based applications with Git-compatible versioning.

This module implements a MirageOS backend for Irmin with full read and write compatibility with Git repositories. It enables direct synchronization between Irmin stores and Git remotes, supporting operations like push, pull, and clone over standard Git protocols. Use it to build versioned, distributed applications that interoperate seamlessly with Git infrastructure.
